&gt; Yes, there is. Here is a sketch of the solution.
&gt;
&gt; 1. Add a constructor to your TestCase subclass that accepts the
&gt; parameters you want to use for each test. Store those parameters
&gt; in the test fixture (instance variables).
&gt; 2. Create ONE test method that uses the test fixture and runs the test.
&gt; 3. Create a suite() method that loops through your test data and
&gt; uses your new constructor to push test data into the test fixture.
&gt;
&gt; You can code your suite() method any way you want: it can read
&gt; data from a file or a database, for example.
&gt;
&gt; A more complete example will be available in the book &quot;JUnit
&gt; Cookbook&quot; sometime in late 2003/early 2004. :)
